<subSubSection id="F5902BAAFF9FD93817D6F927FB56C05D" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="299" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="BD357821FF9FD93917D6F927FC47C7A3" blockId="2.[151,1437,1736,2015]" box="[199,1011,1736,1763]" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="8FFEA433FF9FD93917D6F927FE80C7A2" bold="true" box="[199,308,1736,1762]" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">Host ant.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="7A8A03A2FF9FD939162AF926FC59C7A3" authority="(Kuznetsov-Ugamsky, 1928)" baseAuthorityName="Kuznetsov-Ugamsky" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[315,1005,1736,1763]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Lasius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capitatus" subGenus="Dendrolasius">
<emphasis id="8FFEA433FF9FD939162AF926FE30C7A2" box="[315,388,1737,1762]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">Lasius</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="8FFEA433FF9FD9391684F927FD9FC7A2" box="[405,555,1736,1762]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">Dendrolasius</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="8FFEA433FF9FD939152AF926FD16C7A2" box="[571,674,1737,1762]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">capitatus</emphasis>
(Kuznetsov-Ugamsky, 1928)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD357821FF9FD93917D6F903FDACC66A" blockId="2.[151,1437,1736,2015]" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="8FFEA433FF9FD93917D6F903FE06C646" bold="true" box="[199,434,1772,1798]" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">Comparative notes.</emphasis>
Since the female of this species is not yet known, all of the following comparisons between species are given for males.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD357821FF9FD93917D6F8DBFC16C69E" blockId="2.[151,1437,1736,2015]" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">
The new species is close to 
<taxonomicName id="7A8A03A2FF9FD9391511F8DAFD7FC60E" authorityName="Hlavac, Sugaya &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2002" box="[512,715,1844,1870]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Batristilbus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrotibialis">
<emphasis id="8FFEA433FF9FD9391511F8DAFD7FC60E" box="[512,715,1844,1870]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">D. monstrotibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7A8A03A2FF9FD9391413F8DAFC29C60E" authorityName="Nomura" authorityYear="2008" box="[770,925,1844,1870]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Dendrolasiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nishikawai">
<emphasis id="8FFEA433FF9FD9391413F8DAFC29C60E" box="[770,925,1844,1870]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">D. nishikawai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the structure of the modified metafemora. It differs from both of these species by the lack of the distinct modifications of the metatibiae and somewhat larger body sizes (
<taxonomicName id="7A8A03A2FF9FD939160DF892FE52C6D6" authorityName="Hlavac, Sugaya &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2002" box="[284,486,1916,1942]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Batristilbus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrotibialis">
<emphasis id="8FFEA433FF9FD939160DF892FE52C6D6" box="[284,486,1916,1942]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">D. monstrotibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– 
<quantity id="7A72D5C4FF9FD9391510F893FDECC6D7" box="[513,600,1916,1943]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7A8A03A2FF9FD9391572F892FD4AC6D6" authorityName="Nomura" authorityYear="2008" box="[611,766,1916,1942]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Dendrolasiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nishikawai">
<emphasis id="8FFEA433FF9FD9391572F892FD4AC6D6" box="[611,766,1916,1942]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">D. nishikawai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– 
<quantity id="7A72D5C4FF9FD9391408F893FC17C6D7" box="[793,931,1916,1943]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="2.55" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="2.5">2.5–2.6 mm</quantity>
). In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="7A8A03A2FF9FD939132DF892FB19C6D6" authority="Kurbatov &amp; Kovalev, 2022" authorityName="Kurbatov &amp; Kovalev" authorityYear="2022" box="[1084,1197,1916,1942]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Dendrolasiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subitus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="8FFEA433FF9FD939132DF892FB19C6D6" box="[1084,1197,1916,1942]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">D. subitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="94CD1948FF9FD93913A5F892FB5BC6D7" box="[1204,1263,1917,1943]" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="7A8A03A2FF9FD9391290F892FEF4C6FA" authorityName="Hlavac, Sugaya &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2002" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Batristilbus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrotibialis">
<emphasis id="8FFEA433FF9FD9391290F892FEF4C6FA" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">D. monstrotibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the straight, non-emarginate mesotibiae; from 
<taxonomicName id="7A8A03A2FF9FD939147EF84EFBBEC6FA" authorityName="Nomura" authorityYear="2008" box="[879,1034,1952,1978]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Dendrolasiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nishikawai">
<emphasis id="8FFEA433FF9FD939147EF84EFBBEC6FA" box="[879,1034,1952,1978]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="298">D. nishikawai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of an apical spur of the mesotibiae, and the presence of a denticle on the metatrochanters.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD357821FF9ED93817D6FF78FB56C05D" blockId="3.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="299">
It is interesting to note that the aedeagi of the known 
<taxonomicName id="7A8A03A2FF9ED9381430FF78FBFDC1F1" box="[801,1097,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Dendrolasiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="8FFEA433FF9ED9381430FF78FC44C1F1" box="[801,1008,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="299">Dendrolasiophilus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
are almost identical, differing weakly in the shape of serrate apicolateral lobe and general proportions. In the species compared, the ratio of the total length of the aedeagus to the maximum width of the basal capsule is 
<quantity id="7A72D5C4FF9ED93814DDFF31FBADC1B9" box="[972,1049,222,249]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.699" pageId="3" pageNumber="299" unit="in" value="1.85">1.85 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="7A8A03A2FF9ED938130EFF30FB24C1B9" authorityName="Kurbatov &amp; Kovalev" authorityYear="2022" box="[1055,1168,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Dendrolasiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subitus">
<emphasis id="8FFEA433FF9ED938130EFF30FB24C1B9" box="[1055,1168,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="299">D. subitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<quantity id="7A72D5C4FF9ED938138FFF31FB5FC1B9" box="[1182,1259,222,249]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.445" pageId="3" pageNumber="299" unit="in" value="1.75">1.75 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="7A8A03A2FF9ED93813E0FF30FF0BC05D" authorityName="Hlavac, Sugaya &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2002" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Batristilbus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrotibialis">
<emphasis id="8FFEA433FF9ED93813E0FF30FF0BC05D" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="299">D. monstrotibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<quantity id="7A72D5C4FF9ED93817ECFEEDFEFFC05D" box="[253,331,258,285]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.937" pageId="3" pageNumber="299" unit="in" value="1.55">1.55 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="7A8A03A2FF9ED9381643FEECFE59C05D" authorityName="Nomura" authorityYear="2008" box="[338,493,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Dendrolasiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nishikawai">
<emphasis id="8FFEA433FF9ED9381643FEECFE59C05D" box="[338,493,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="299">D. nishikawai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; although the variability of this parameter has not yet been studied.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F5902BAAFF9ED93817D6FEC8FC2BC025" pageId="3" pageNumber="299" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="BD357821FF9ED93817D6FEC8FC2BC025" blockId="3.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis id="8FFEA433FF9ED93817D6FEC8FEFAC001" bold="true" box="[199,334,295,321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="299">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a Latin adjective in English meaning 
<emphasis id="8FFEA433FF9ED9381313FEC8FB34C001" box="[1026,1152,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="299">unexpected</emphasis>
or 
<emphasis id="8FFEA433FF9ED93813B9FEC8FB43C001" box="[1192,1271,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="299">sudden</emphasis>
, reflecting the surprise discovery of this remarkable species in the Russian Far East.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
